		{"id":"a2e868df1d8fc623","type":"text","text":"### üñºÔ∏è **When to Use HTML vs. CSS for Images**\n\n* **Decorative images** (like background gradients or textures): Use **CSS**.\n* **Content images** (those adding meaning or context): Use **HTML** with the `<img>` tag.\n\n---\n\n### üì∏ **Basic `<img>` Tag Usage**\n\n```html\n<img src=\"images/eve.png\" alt=\"Eve\" />\n```\n\n* `src`: Path to the image (required).\n* `alt`: Alternative text for screen readers, search engines, or if the image fails to load (required for accessibility).\n\n---\n\n### üñ•Ô∏è **Responsive Images**\n\nTwo main methods:\n\n#### 1. **`srcset` with `<img>`**\n\n```html\n<img src=\"images/eve.png\" alt=\"Eve\"\n     srcset=\"images/eve.png 400w, images/eve-xl.jpg 800w\"\n     sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 400px, 800px\" />\n```\n\n* Loads different image sizes depending on device resolution and viewport.\n\n#### 2. **`<picture>` Element**\n\n```html\n<picture>\n  <source srcset=\"images/eve.png\" media=\"(max-width: 800px)\" />\n  <source srcset=\"images/eve-xl.jpg\" />\n  <img src=\"images/eve.png\" alt=\"Eve\" />\n</picture>\n```\n\n* Offers more flexibility (e.g., format switching like WebP/fallback).\n* Browser selects the first matching `<source>`.\n\n---\n\n### üöÄ **Image Optimization Features**\n\n* `width` & `height` attributes help **reduce layout shifts**.\n* `loading=\"lazy\"` enables **lazy loading**, improving performance.\n* **SVG images**:\n\n  * Can be embedded with `<img>` or inline with `<svg>`.\n  * Use `role=\"img\"` on `<img>` for SVGs due to accessibility issues on some platforms.\n\n---\n\n### üìù **Semantic Grouping with `<figure>` and `<figcaption>`**\n\nUse when an image has a **related description**:\n\n```html\n<figure>\n  <img src=\"sunset.jpg\" alt=\"Sunset over mountains\" />\n  <figcaption>Photo taken from the summit of Mount Fuji.</figcaption>\n</figure>\n```\n\n* `<figure>` groups visual media with a caption.\n* `<figcaption>` should be **first or last child** inside `<figure>`.\n\n---\n\n### ‚ö†Ô∏è **Other Notes**\n\n* Use semantic HTML (`alt`, `role`, etc.) for **accessibility and SEO**.\n* Don't use XML-style self-closing tags (like `<img />`) in HTML‚Äîjust use `<img>`.","x":-160,"y":-777,"width":680,"height":1657},
